goal:
Architect and implement a major upgrade to the 'Celestial Ascent' game in '/Users/abhisheksonkar/Documents/CelestialAscent/index.html'. Make the level significantly more fun and complex. 

PROPS TO ADD:
1. Swinging Basket: A platform suspended by a physics rope that swings back and forth. 
2. Air Flow Rings: Circular rings that apply a strong directional force when the player passes through them.
3. Expanded Level: Design a path with at least 10 platforms using different types (Moving, Breakable, Static).

TECHNICAL:
- Maintain WASD and Spacebar Jump Charge mechanics.
- Ensure all new props have synced Cannon.js physics bodies.
- Verify the code is complete and open it in the browser.
plan: Analyze the existing CelestialAscent game code to understand current player controls, physics implementation, and level structure
Design the expanded level layout with at least 10 platforms, mapping positions and types (moving, breakable, static)
Implement the Swinging Basket: Create basic HTML structure and CSS styling for the swinging platform
Add physics to Swinging Basket: Implement Cannon.js body with rope/pendulum constraints and swing mechanics
Implement Air Flow Rings: Create HTML/CSS structure for directional force rings with visual effects
Add physics to Air Flow Rings: Implement Cannon.js body with directional force field effect when player enters
Integrate new props into level: Place Swinging Basket and Air Flow Rings at strategic positions in the expanded layout
Update player collision detection to properly interact with new props (Swinging Basket and Air Flow Rings)
Test and balance physics: Verify swinging mechanics feel natural and air flow forces are appropriately strong
Implement level progression: Connect all platforms and props into a coherent, challenging path
Final integration test: Verify all props work together, player controls remain consistent, and level is completable
Open the updated index.html in browser and perform comprehensive gameplay testing
